<i>I asked Corporal Henderson
<i>of the United States Marine Corps</i></i>

2282
01:55:38,897 --> 01:55:40,774
<i>to join me on Capitol Hill</i>

2283
01:55:40,941 --> 01:55:44,570
<i>to see how many members of Congress
<i>we could convince</i></i>

2284
01:55:44,736 --> 01:55:47,155
<i>to enlist their children to go to Iraq.</i>

2285
01:55:47,322 --> 01:55:49,032
Congressman, I'm Michael Moore.

2286
01:55:49,199 --> 01:55:51,869
Hey Michael, how are you doing?
I'm good, John Tanner.

2287
01:55:52,035 --> 01:55:54,538
Yeah, nice to meet you,
very nice to meet you.

2288
01:55:54,705 --> 01:55:56,874
-What are you doing?
-Well, I'm here with Cpl. Henderson.

2289
01:55:57,040 --> 01:56:00,043
-U.S. Marine Corps.
-Corporal, I was in the Navy years ago.

2290
01:56:00,210 --> 01:56:03,046
-Okay, Sir!
-1968 to 72.

2291
01:56:03,213 --> 01:56:05,090
We had Marines guarding the base.

2292
01:56:05,257 --> 01:56:07,092
-[Moore] You have kids?
-[Tanner] Yeah.

2293
01:56:07,259 --> 01:56:11,180
Is here anyway we can get them to enlist
and go over and help out with the effort?

2294
01:56:11,346 --> 01:56:12,681
I have all the brochures.

2295
01:56:12,848 --> 01:56:14,474
One of them got two children.

2296
01:56:15,267 --> 01:56:16,602
Oh, oh, well!

2297
01:56:16,768 --> 01:56:19,188
See, there's not that many Congressmen
that've got kids over there.

2298
01:56:19,354 --> 01:56:20,814
And in fact, only one.

2299
01:56:20,981 --> 01:56:25,986
So we just thought maybe you guys
should send your kids there first.

2300
01:56:26,153 --> 01:56:27,946
What do you think about that idea?

2301
01:56:28,113 --> 01:56:30,115
-I don't disagree with you.
-Oh, you don't?

2302
01:56:30,282 --> 01:56:32,618
Oh good, well, here,
take some brochures then, here.

2303
01:56:32,784 --> 01:56:35,037
At least take a Marine brochure,
and pass it around.

2304
01:56:35,204 --> 01:56:36,121
Yeah!

2305
01:56:36,288 --> 01:56:39,625
Encourage fellow members,
if they're for the war, to get behind it,

2306
01:56:39,791 --> 01:56:41,043
and send their own!

2307
01:56:41,210 --> 01:56:43,670
-Thank you, Mike.
-Thank you, Sir, thank you very much.

2308
01:56:45,130 --> 01:56:47,549
Congressman! Michael Moore.

2309
01:56:47,716 --> 01:56:48,967
-How are you doing?
-Good, good!

2310
01:56:49,134 --> 01:56:53,138
I'm trying to get members of Congress
to get their kids to enlist in the Army

2311
01:56:53,305 --> 01:56:54,806
and go over to Iraq.

2312
01:56:56,141 --> 01:56:59,144
Congressman! Congressman!

2313
