<i>Of course, not a single member of Congress
<i>wanted to sacrifice their child</i></i>

2321
01:57:19,998 --> 01:57:21,500
<i>for the war in Iraq.</i>

2322
01:57:22,084 --> 01:57:23,210
<i>And who could blame them?</i>

2323
01:57:23,377 --> 01:57:24,253
[music intensifies]

2324
01:57:24,419 --> 01:57:27,548
<i>Who would want to give up their child.
<i>Would you?</i></i>

2325
01:57:28,590 --> 01:57:29,716
<i>Would he?</i>

2326
01:57:32,469 --> 01:57:34,304
<i>I've always been amazed
<i>that the very people</i></i>

2327
01:57:34,805 --> 01:57:38,350
<i>forced to live in the worst parts of town,
<i>go to the worst schools</i></i>

2328
01:57:38,934 --> 01:57:41,270
<i>and who have it the hardest,</i>

2329
01:57:41,436 --> 01:57:45,023
<i>are always the first to step up
<i>to defend that very system.</i></i>

2330
01:57:45,941 --> 01:57:48,902
<i>They serve so that we don't have to.</i>

2331
01:57:49,528 --> 01:57:51,530
<i>They offer to give up their lives</i>

2332
01:57:52,197 --> 01:57:54,157
<i>so that we can be free.</i>

2333
01:57:55,242 --> 01:57:57,786
<i>It is remarkable, their gift to us.</i>

2334
01:57:58,787 --> 01:58:00,789
<i>And all they ask for in return,</i>

2335
01:58:01,957 --> 01:58:04,543
<i>is that we never send them
<i>into harm's way.</i></i>

2336
01:58:05,252 --> 01:58:08,172
<i>Unless it's absolutely necessary.</i>

2337
01:58:10,132 --> 01:58:12,467
<i>Will they ever trust us again?</i>

2338
01:58:13,677 --> 01:58:15,721
He had used weapons.

2339
01:58:15,888 --> 01:58:17,014
We know where they are,

2340
01:58:17,181 --> 01:58:19,683
they're in the area
around Tikrit and Baghdad,

2341
01:58:19,850 --> 01:58:21,602
and East, West, South, and North.

2342
01:58:21,768 --> 01:58:26,064
There is a tie between Iraq
and what happened on 9/11.

2343
01:58:26,565 --> 01:58:31,320
The struggle can only end with
their complete and permanent destruction.

2344
01:58:31,486 --> 01:58:34,948
We waged a war
to save a civilization itself.

2345
01:58:36,783 --> 01:58:38,368
We did not seek it,

2346
01:58:39,453 --> 01:58:42,623
but we will fight it, and we will prevail.

2347
01:58:43,498 --> 01:58:45,501
[Michael Moore]
<i>George Orwell once wrote</i>

2348
01:58:45,667 --> 01:58:50,255
<i>that it's not a matter of whether the war
<i>is not real or if it is.</i></i>

2349
01:58:50,714 --> 01:58:52,549
<i>Victory is not possible.</i>

2350
01:58:53,800 --> 01:58:56,094
<i>The war is not meant to be won.</i>

2351
01:58:56,261 --> 01:58:58,222
<i>It is meant to be continuous.</i>

2352
01:58:59,598 --> 01:59:04,645
<i>A hierarchical society is only possible
<i>on the basis of poverty and ignorance.</i></i>

2353
01:59:05,979 --> 01:59:08,315
<i>This new version is the past</i>

2354
01:59:08,482 --> 01:59:10,984
<i>and no different past
<i>can ever have existed.</i></i>

2355
01:59:13,570 --> 01:59:14,655
<i>In principle, the war effort</i>

2356
01:59:14,821 --> 01:59:18,909
<i>is always planned to keep society
<i>on the brink of starvation.</i></i>

2357
01:59:19,326 --> 01:59:22,412
<i>The war is waged by the ruling group
<i>against its own subjects,</i></i>

2358
01:59:23,705 --> 01:59:25,415
<i>and its object is not the victory</i>

2359
01:59:25,582 --> 01:59:29,378
<i>over either Eurasia
<i>or East Asia,</i></i>

2360
01:59:29,545 --> 01:59:33,090
<i>but to keep
<i>the very structure of society intact.</i></i>

2361
01:59:33,423 --> 01:59:35,175
There's an old saying in Tennessee,

2362
01:59:35,342 --> 01:59:36,927
I know it's in Texas,
probably in Tennessee,

2363
